<li id="cite_note-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-89">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Shearburn Family Tree, <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://trees.ancestry.com/tree/780374/person/-778444995">http://trees.ancestry.com/tree/780374/person/-778444995</a>; England &amp; Wales, Death Index: 1916-2005: Death Registration Month/Year: 1920. Age at death (estimated):58; Registration district: Colchester Inferred County: Essex Volume: 4a Page: 731.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-90">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Simon Shearburn, e-mail, (18 January 2010). However, as the Spanish flu pandemic had abated by June 1920, six months before Peter's death, the family tradition may need to be discounted.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-91"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-91">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">1871 England Census: Class: RG10; Piece: 695; Folio: 86; Page: 11; GSU roll: 823337.</span></li>
